      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Chemistry Insight\n\nThe dominance of **amino acids** and **aliphatic amines** reflects the importance of nitrogen-donor ligands in coordination chemistry — the lone pair on nitrogen is an excellent σ-donor for metal binding. **Pyridines** rank similarly high thanks to their aromatic N-donor character and widespread use in catalysis and supramolecular chemistry. The strong representation of **carboxylic acids** highlights the role of hard oxygen donors, particularly for binding oxophilic metals like lanthanides and early transition metals.\n\n*Source: NIST SRD-46 (Standard Reference Database 46 — Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes)*",
